{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"This is my first time at TED. Normally, as an advertising man,"},{"time":3000,"text":"I actually speak at TED Evil, which is TED's secret sister"},{"time":6000,"text":"that pays all the bills."},{"time":9000,"text":"It's held every two years in Burma."},{"time":12000,"text":"And I particularly remember a really good speech"},{"time":15000,"text":"by Kim Jong Il on how to get teens smoking again."},{"time":18000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20000,"text":"But, actually, it's suddenly come to me after years working in the business,"},{"time":22000,"text":"that what we create in advertising,"},{"time":25000,"text":"which is intangible value -- you might call it perceived value,"},{"time":27000,"text":"you might call it badge value, subjective value,"},{"time":30000,"text":"intangible value of some kind --"},{"time":32000,"text":"gets rather a bad rap."},{"time":34000,"text":"If you think about it, if you want to live in a world in the future"},{"time":36000,"text":"where there are fewer material goods, you basically have two choices."},{"time":40000,"text":"You can either live in a world which is poorer,"},{"time":42000,"text":"which people in general don't like."},{"time":44000,"text":"Or you can live in a world where actually intangible value"},{"time":47000,"text":"constitutes a greater part of overall value,"},{"time":51000,"text":"that actually intangible value, in many ways"},{"time":53000,"text":"is a very, very fine substitute"},{"time":55000,"text":"for using up labor or limited resources"},{"time":58000,"text":"in the creation of things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"Here is one example. This is a train which goes from London to Paris."},{"time":63000,"text":"The question was given to a bunch of engineers,"},{"time":65000,"text":"about 15 years ago, \"How do we make the journey to Paris better?\""},{"time":69000,"text":"And they came up with a very good engineering solution,"},{"time":71000,"text":"which was to spend six billion pounds"},{"time":73000,"text":"building completely new tracks"},{"time":75000,"text":"from London to the coast,"},{"time":77000,"text":"and knocking about 40 minutes off a three-and-half-hour journey time."},{"time":81000,"text":"Now, call me Mister Picky. I'm just an ad man ..."},{"time":83000,"text":"... but it strikes me as a slightly unimaginative way of improving a train journey"},{"time":87000,"text":"merely to make it shorter."},{"time":89000,"text":"Now what is the hedonic opportunity cost"},{"time":92000,"text":"on spending six billion pounds on those railway tracks?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":94000,"text":"Here is my naive advertising man's suggestion."},{"time":97000,"text":"What you should in fact do is employ all of the world's top male"},{"time":99000,"text":"and female supermodels,"},{"time":101000,"text":"pay them to walk the length of the train, handing out free Chateau Petrus"},{"time":105000,"text":"for the entire duration of the journey."},{"time":107000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":109000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":110000,"text":"Now, you'll still have about three billion pounds left in change,"},{"time":114000,"text":"and people will ask for the trains to be slowed down."},{"time":117000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"Now, here is another naive advertising man's question again."},{"time":122000,"text":"And this shows that engineers,"},{"time":124000,"text":"medical people, scientific people,"},{"time":126000,"text":"have an obsession with solving the problems of reality,"},{"time":129000,"text":"when actually most problems, once you reach a basic level of wealth"},{"time":132000,"text":"in society, most problems are actually problems of perception."},{"time":135000,"text":"So I'll ask you another question."},{"time":137000,"text":"What on earth is wrong with placebos?"},{"time":139000,"text":"They seem fantastic to me. They cost very little to develop."},{"time":141000,"text":"They work extraordinarily well."},{"time":144000,"text":"They have no side effects,"},{"time":146000,"text":"or if they do, they're imaginary, so you can safely ignore them."},{"time":148000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":150000,"text":"So I was discussing this. And I actually went to the Marginal Revolution blog"},{"time":152000,"text":"by Tyler Cowen. I don't know if anybody knows it."},{"time":154000,"text":"Someone was actually suggesting that you can take this concept further,"},{"time":157000,"text":"and actually produce placebo education."},{"time":159000,"text":"The point is that education doesn't actually work by teaching you things."},{"time":163000,"text":"It actually works by giving you the impression"},{"time":165000,"text":"that you've had a very good education, which gives you an insane sense"},{"time":167000,"text":"of unwarranted self-confidence,"},{"time":169000,"text":"which then makes you very, very successful in later life."},{"time":172000,"text":"So, welcome to Oxford, ladies and gentlemen."},{"time":175000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":177000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":178000,"text":"But, actually, the point of placebo education is interesting."},{"time":181000,"text":"How many problems of life can be solved"},{"time":183000,"text":"actually by tinkering with perception,"},{"time":185000,"text":"rather than that tedious, hardworking and messy business"},{"time":187000,"text":"of actually trying to change reality?"},{"time":190000,"text":"Here's a great example from history. I've heard this attributed to several other kings,"},{"time":193000,"text":"but doing a bit of historical research,"},{"time":195000,"text":"it seems to be Fredrick the Great."},{"time":197000,"text":"Fredrick the Great of Prussia was very, very keen"},{"time":199000,"text":"for the Germans to adopt the potato and to eat it,"},{"time":202000,"text":"because he realized that if you had two sources of carbohydrate,"},{"time":204000,"text":"wheat and potatoes, you get less price volatility in bread."},{"time":208000,"text":"And you get a far lower risk of famine,"},{"time":210000,"text":"because you actually had two crops to fall back on, not one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212000,"text":"The only problem is: potatoes, if you think about it, look pretty disgusting."},{"time":215000,"text":"And also, 18th century Prussians ate very, very few vegetables --"},{"time":219000,"text":"rather like contemporary Scottish people."},{"time":221000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":223000,"text":"So, actually, he tried making it compulsory."},{"time":226000,"text":"The Prussian peasantry said,"},{"time":228000,"text":"\"We can't even get the dogs to eat these damn things."},{"time":230000,"text":"They are absolutely disgusting and they're good for nothing.\""},{"time":232000,"text":"There are even records of people being executed"},{"time":234000,"text":"for refusing to grow potatoes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236000,"text":"So he tried plan B."},{"time":238000,"text":"He tried the marketing solution, which is he declared the potato"},{"time":240000,"text":"as a royal vegetable, and none but the royal family could consume it."},{"time":243000,"text":"And he planted it in a royal potato patch,"},{"time":245000,"text":"with guards who had instructions"},{"time":247000,"text":"to guard over it, night and day,"},{"time":249000,"text":"but with secret instructions not to guard it very well."},{"time":252000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":253000,"text":"Now, 18th century peasants know that there is one"},{"time":255000,"text":"pretty safe rule in life, which is if something is worth guarding,"},{"time":257000,"text":"it's worth stealing."},{"time":259000,"text":"Before long, there was a massive underground"},{"time":261000,"text":"potato-growing operation in Germany."},{"time":263000,"text":"What he'd effectively done is he'd re-branded the potato."},{"time":267000,"text":"It was an absolute masterpiece."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269000,"text":"I told this story and a gentleman from Turkey came up to me and said,"},{"time":271000,"text":"\"Very, very good marketer, Fredrick the Great. But not a patch on Ataturk.\""},{"time":275000,"text":"Ataturk, rather like Nicolas Sarkozy,"},{"time":277000,"text":"was very keen to discourage the wearing of a veil,"},{"time":279000,"text":"in Turkey, to modernize it."},{"time":281000,"text":"Now, boring people would have just simply banned the veil."},{"time":284000,"text":"But that would have ended up with a lot of awful kickback"},{"time":286000,"text":"and a hell of a lot of resistance."},{"time":288000,"text":"Ataturk was a lateral thinker."},{"time":290000,"text":"He made it compulsory for prostitutes to wear the veil."},{"time":293000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":298000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":300000,"text":"I can't verify that fully, but it does not matter."},{"time":302000,"text":"There is your environmental problem solved, by the way, guys:"},{"time":304000,"text":"All convicted child molesters"},{"time":306000,"text":"have to drive a Porsche Cayenne."},{"time":308000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":313000,"text":"What Ataturk realized actually is two very fundamental things."},{"time":316000,"text":"Which is that, actually, first one,"},{"time":318000,"text":"all value is actually relative."},{"time":321000,"text":"All value is perceived value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323000,"text":"For those of you who don't speak Spanish, jugo de naranja -- it's actually the Spanish for \"orange juice.\""},{"time":325000,"text":"Because actually it's not the dollar. It's actually the peso"},{"time":327000,"text":"in Buenos Aires. Very clever Buenos Aires street vendors"},{"time":330000,"text":"decided to practice price discrimination"},{"time":332000,"text":"to the detriment of any passing gringo tourists."},{"time":335000,"text":"As an advertising man, I have to admire that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337000,"text":"But the first thing is that all value is subjective."},{"time":341000,"text":"Second point is that persuasion is often better than compulsion."},{"time":344000,"text":"These funny signs that flash your speed at you,"},{"time":346000,"text":"some of the new ones, on the bottom right,"},{"time":348000,"text":"now actually show a smiley face or a frowny face,"},{"time":351000,"text":"to act as an emotional trigger."},{"time":353000,"text":"What's fascinating about these signs is they cost about 10 percent"},{"time":355000,"text":"of the running cost of a conventional speed camera,"},{"time":358000,"text":"but they prevent twice as many accidents."},{"time":360000,"text":"So, the bizarre thing, which is baffling"},{"time":362000,"text":"to conventional, classically trained economists,"},{"time":364000,"text":"is that a weird little smiley face"},{"time":366000,"text":"has a better effect on changing your behavior"},{"time":368000,"text":"than the threat of a £60 fine and three penalty points."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"Tiny little behavioral economics detail:"},{"time":375000,"text":"in Italy, penalty points go backwards."},{"time":378000,"text":"You start with 12 and they take them away."},{"time":380000,"text":"Because they found that loss aversion"},{"time":382000,"text":"is a more powerful influence on people's behavior."},{"time":384000,"text":"In Britain we tend to feel, \"Whoa! Got another three!\""},{"time":387000,"text":"Not so in Italy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389000,"text":"Another fantastic case of creating intangible value"},{"time":392000,"text":"to replace actual or material value, which remember, is what,"},{"time":395000,"text":"after all, the environmental movement needs to be about:"},{"time":397000,"text":"This again is from Prussia, from, I think, about 1812, 1813."},{"time":400000,"text":"The wealthy Prussians, to help in the war against the French,"},{"time":403000,"text":"were encouraged to give in all their jewelry."},{"time":405000,"text":"And it was replaced with replica jewelry"},{"time":408000,"text":"made of cast iron."},{"time":410000,"text":"Here's one: \"Gold gab ich für Eisen, 1813.\""},{"time":414000,"text":"The interesting thing is that for 50 years hence,"},{"time":416000,"text":"the highest status jewelry you could wear in Prussia"},{"time":418000,"text":"wasn't made of gold or diamonds."},{"time":420000,"text":"It was made of cast iron."},{"time":422000,"text":"Because actually, never mind the actual intrinsic value"},{"time":424000,"text":"of having gold jewelry. This actually"},{"time":426000,"text":"had symbolic value, badge value."},{"time":428000,"text":"It said that your family had made a great sacrifice in the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431000,"text":"So, the modern equivalent would of course be this."},{"time":433000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":434000,"text":"But, actually, there is a thing, just as there are Veblen goods,"},{"time":437000,"text":"where the value of the good depends on it being expensive and rare --"},{"time":440000,"text":"there are opposite kind of things"},{"time":442000,"text":"where actually the value in them depends on them being"},{"time":444000,"text":"ubiquitous, classless and minimalistic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447000,"text":"If you think about it, Shakerism was a proto-environmental movement."},{"time":450000,"text":"Adam Smith talks about 18th century America,"},{"time":452000,"text":"where the prohibition against visible displays of wealth was so great,"},{"time":456000,"text":"it was almost a block in the economy in New England,"},{"time":458000,"text":"because even wealthy farmers could find nothing to spend their money on"},{"time":461000,"text":"without incurring the displeasure of their neighbors."},{"time":464000,"text":"It's perfectly possible to create these social pressures"},{"time":466000,"text":"which lead to more egalitarian societies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469000,"text":"What's also interesting, if you look at products"},{"time":471000,"text":"that have a high component"},{"time":473000,"text":"of what you might call messaging value,"},{"time":475000,"text":"a high component of intangible value, versus their intrinsic value:"},{"time":478000,"text":"They are often quite egalitarian."},{"time":481000,"text":"In terms of dress, denim is perhaps the perfect example of something"},{"time":484000,"text":"which replaces material value with symbolic value."},{"time":488000,"text":"Coca-Cola. A bunch of you may be a load of pinkos,"},{"time":490000,"text":"and you may not like the Coca-Cola company,"},{"time":492000,"text":"but it's worth remembering Andy Warhol's point about Coke."},{"time":494000,"text":"What Warhol said about Coke is, he said,"},{"time":496000,"text":"\"What I really like about Coca-Cola is the president of the United States"},{"time":498000,"text":"can't get a better Coke than the bum on the corner of the street.\""},{"time":502000,"text":"Now, that is, actually, when you think about it -- we take it for granted --"},{"time":504000,"text":"it's actually a remarkable achievement,"},{"time":506000,"text":"to produce something that's that democratic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509000,"text":"Now, we basically have to change our views slightly."},{"time":512000,"text":"There is a basic view that real value involves making things,"},{"time":515000,"text":"involves labor. It involves engineering."},{"time":518000,"text":"It involves limited raw materials."},{"time":521000,"text":"And that what we add on top is kind of false. It's a fake version."},{"time":524000,"text":"And there is a reason for some suspicion and uncertainly about it."},{"time":527000,"text":"It patently veers toward propaganda."},{"time":530000,"text":"However, what we do have now"},{"time":532000,"text":"is a much more variegated media ecosystem"},{"time":535000,"text":"in which to kind of create this kind of value, and it's much fairer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538000,"text":"When I grew up, this was basically the media environment of my childhood"},{"time":540000,"text":"as translated into food."},{"time":542000,"text":"You had a monopoly supplier. On the left,"},{"time":544000,"text":"you have Rupert Murdoch, or the BBC."},{"time":546000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":547000,"text":"And on your right you have a dependent public"},{"time":549000,"text":"which is pathetically grateful for anything you give it."},{"time":552000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":554000,"text":"Nowadays, the user is actually involved."},{"time":557000,"text":"This is actually what's called, in the digital world, \"user-generated content.\""},{"time":560000,"text":"Although it's called agriculture in the world of food."},{"time":562000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":563000,"text":"This is actually called a mash-up,"},{"time":565000,"text":"where you take content that someone else has produced"},{"time":567000,"text":"and you do something new with it."},{"time":569000,"text":"In the world of food we call it cooking."},{"time":572000,"text":"This is food 2.0,"},{"time":574000,"text":"which is food you produce for the purpose of sharing it with other people."},{"time":577000,"text":"This is mobile food. British are very good at that."},{"time":580000,"text":"Fish and chips in newspaper, the Cornish Pasty,"},{"time":582000,"text":"the pie, the sandwich."},{"time":584000,"text":"We invented the whole lot of them."},{"time":586000,"text":"We're not very good at food in general. Italians do great food,"},{"time":588000,"text":"but it's not very portable, generally."},{"time":590000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":595000,"text":"I only learned this the other day. The Earl of Sandwich didn't invent the sandwich."},{"time":597000,"text":"He actually invented the toasty. But then, the Earl of Toasty would be a ridiculous name."},{"time":600000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":601000,"text":"Finally, we have contextual communication."},{"time":603000,"text":"Now, the reason I show you Pernod -- it's only one example."},{"time":605000,"text":"Every country has a contextual alcoholic drink. In France it's Pernod."},{"time":609000,"text":"It tastes great within the borders of that country,"},{"time":611000,"text":"but absolute shite if you take it anywhere else."},{"time":614000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":616000,"text":"Unicum in Hungary, for example."},{"time":618000,"text":"The Greeks have actually managed to produce something called Retsina,"},{"time":620000,"text":"which even tastes shite when you're in Greece."},{"time":622000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":624000,"text":"But so much communication now is contextual"},{"time":626000,"text":"that the capacity for actually nudging people,"},{"time":628000,"text":"for giving them better information -- B.J. Fogg,"},{"time":630000,"text":"at the University of Stanford, makes the point"},{"time":632000,"text":"that actually the mobile phone is --"},{"time":634000,"text":"He's invented the phrase, \"persuasive technologies.\""},{"time":636000,"text":"He believes the mobile phone, by being location-specific,"},{"time":639000,"text":"contextual, timely and immediate,"},{"time":641000,"text":"is simply the greatest persuasive technology device ever invented."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644000,"text":"Now, if we have all these tools at our disposal,"},{"time":646000,"text":"we simply have to ask the question,"},{"time":648000,"text":"and Thaler and Sunstein have, of how we can use these more intelligently."},{"time":651000,"text":"I'll give you one example."},{"time":654000,"text":"If you had a large red button of this kind, on the wall of your home,"},{"time":656000,"text":"and every time you pressed it, it saved 50 dollars for you,"},{"time":659000,"text":"put 50 dollars into your pension,"},{"time":661000,"text":"you would save a lot more."},{"time":663000,"text":"The reason is that the interface fundamentally determines"},{"time":665000,"text":"the behavior. Okay?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":667000,"text":"Now, marketing has done a very, very good job of creating"},{"time":670000,"text":"opportunities for impulse buying."},{"time":672000,"text":"Yet we've never created the opportunity for impulse saving."},{"time":676000,"text":"If you did this, more people would save more."},{"time":679000,"text":"It's simply a question of changing the interface"},{"time":681000,"text":"by which people make decisions,"},{"time":683000,"text":"and the very nature of the decisions changes."},{"time":685000,"text":"Obviously, I don't want people to do this,"},{"time":687000,"text":"because as an advertising man I tend to regard saving as just"},{"time":689000,"text":"consumerism needlessly postponed."},{"time":691000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":692000,"text":"But if anybody did want to do that,"},{"time":695000,"text":"that's the kind of thing we need to be thinking about, actually:"},{"time":698000,"text":"fundamental opportunities to change human behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700000,"text":"Now, I've got an example here from Canada."},{"time":703000,"text":"There was a young intern at Ogilvy Canada"},{"time":706000,"text":"called Hunter Somerville,"},{"time":708000,"text":"who was working in improv in Toronto,"},{"time":710000,"text":"and got a part-time job in advertising,"},{"time":712000,"text":"and was given the job of advertising Shreddies."},{"time":715000,"text":"Now this is the most perfect case of creating"},{"time":717000,"text":"intangible, added value,"},{"time":719000,"text":"without changing the product in the slightest."},{"time":722000,"text":"Shreddies is a strange, square, whole-grain cereal,"},{"time":725000,"text":"only available in New Zealand, Canada and Britain."},{"time":729000,"text":"It's Kraft's peculiar way of rewarding loyalty to the crown."},{"time":732000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":735000,"text":"In working out how you could re-launch Shreddies,"},{"time":738000,"text":"he came up with this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747000,"text":"Video: (Buzzer)"},{"time":753000,"text":"Man: Shreddies is supposed to be square."},{"time":756000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":757000,"text":"Woman: Have any of these diamond shapes gone out?"},{"time":760000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":762000,"text":"Voiceover: New Diamond Shreddies cereal."},{"time":764000,"text":"Same 100 percent whole-grain wheat in a delicious diamond shape."},{"time":767000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":771000,"text":"Rory Sutherland: I'm not sure this isn't the most perfect example"},{"time":773000,"text":"of intangible value creation. All it requires is"},{"time":775000,"text":"photons, neurons, and a great idea to create this thing."},{"time":778000,"text":"I would say it's a work of genius."},{"time":780000,"text":"But, naturally, you can't do this kind of thing without a little bit of market research."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"Man: So, Shreddies is actually producing a new product,"},{"time":786000,"text":"which is something very exciting for them."},{"time":789000,"text":"So they are introducing new Diamond Shreddies."},{"time":792000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":797000,"text":"So I just want to get your first impressions when you see that,"},{"time":799000,"text":"when you see the Diamond Shreddies box there."},{"time":802000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":803000,"text":"Woman: Weren't they square?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":805000,"text":"Woman #2: I'm a little bit confused. Woman #3: They look like the squares to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807000,"text":"Man: They -- Yeah, it's all in the appearance."},{"time":809000,"text":"But it's kind of like flipping a six or a nine. Like a six,"},{"time":813000,"text":"if you flip it over it looks like a nine."},{"time":815000,"text":"But a six is very different from a nine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817000,"text":"Woman # 3: Or an \"M\" and a \"W\". Man: An \"M\" and a \"W\", exactly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819000,"text":"Man #2: [unclear]"},{"time":821000,"text":"You just looked like you turned it on its end. But when you see it like that"},{"time":824000,"text":"it's more interesting looking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826000,"text":"Man: Just try both of them."},{"time":828000,"text":"Take a square one there, first."},{"time":831000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":843000,"text":"Man: Which one did you prefer? Man #2: The first one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":845000,"text":"Man: The first one?"},{"time":847000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":849000,"text":"Rory Sutherland: Now, naturally, a debate raged."},{"time":853000,"text":"There were conservative elements in Canada, unsurprisingly,"},{"time":856000,"text":"who actually resented this intrusion."},{"time":858000,"text":"So, eventually, the manufacturers actually"},{"time":860000,"text":"arrived at a compromise, which was the combo pack."},{"time":863000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":865000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":874000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":879000,"text":"If you think it's funny, bear in mind there is an organization called"},{"time":882000,"text":"the American Institute of Wine Economics,"},{"time":885000,"text":"which actually does extensive research into perception of things,"},{"time":887000,"text":"and discovers that except for among"},{"time":889000,"text":"perhaps five or ten percent of the most knowledgeable people,"},{"time":892000,"text":"there is no correlation between quality and enjoyment"},{"time":894000,"text":"in wine,"},{"time":896000,"text":"except when you tell the people how expensive it is,"},{"time":898000,"text":"in which case they tend to enjoy the more expensive stuff more."},{"time":901000,"text":"So drink your wine blind in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904000,"text":"But this is both hysterically funny --"},{"time":906000,"text":"but I think an important philosophical point,"},{"time":908000,"text":"which is, going forward, we need more of this kind of value."},{"time":911000,"text":"We need to spend more time appreciating what already exists,"},{"time":914000,"text":"and less time agonizing over what else we can do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":916000,"text":"Two quotations to more or less end with."},{"time":918000,"text":"One of them is, \"Poetry is when you make new things"},{"time":920000,"text":"familiar and familiar things new.\""},{"time":922000,"text":"Which isn't a bad definition of what our job is,"},{"time":925000,"text":"to help people appreciate what is unfamiliar, but also"},{"time":927000,"text":"to gain a greater appreciation, and place a far higher value on"},{"time":931000,"text":"those things which are already existing."},{"time":933000,"text":"There is some evidence, by the way, that things like social networking help do that."},{"time":936000,"text":"Because they help people share news."},{"time":938000,"text":"They give badge value to everyday little trivial activities."},{"time":942000,"text":"So they actually reduce the need for actually spending great money on display,"},{"time":945000,"text":"and increase the kind of third-party"},{"time":947000,"text":"enjoyment you can get from the smallest, simplest things in life. Which is magic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951000,"text":"The second one is the second G.K. Chesterton quote of this session,"},{"time":954000,"text":"which is, \"We are perishing for want of wonder, not for want of wonders,\""},{"time":957000,"text":"which I think for anybody involved in technology, is perfectly true."},{"time":960000,"text":"And a final thing: When you place a value on things like health,"},{"time":962000,"text":"love, sex and other things,"},{"time":964000,"text":"and learn to place a material value"},{"time":966000,"text":"on what you've previously discounted"},{"time":968000,"text":"for being merely intangible, a thing not seen,"},{"time":971000,"text":"you realize you're much, much wealthier than you ever imagined."},{"time":974000,"text":"Thank you very much indeed."},{"time":976000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}